Abstract: This paper demonstrates that Adam Smith&rsquo;s insights and reasoning can improve the theory of international business, and shed light on its academic practices. Smith was a system builder; his theory of knowledge underpinned his entire oeuvre, and understanding his systematic approach can help current international business to achieve a similarly coherent body of theory. Smith&rsquo;s approach sheds direct light on decision-making in multinational enterprises, and on cultural distance (the &ldquo;liability of foreignness&rdquo;). Combining these two areas yields new Smithian insights into multinational enterprises from emerging countries.
